  "time_ut": 1656743571,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dda\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister tells how to bring rice from the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Trade Minister Nalin Fernando said that it has been decided to import between 75,000 and 100,000 metric tons of rice every month.",
        "He also mentioned that this step is taken to prevent food shortage.",
        "Meanwhile, the Ministry of Agriculture says that 65000 tons of urea from India is to be received in this country on the 6th."
      ],
      "title_ents": [],
      "body_line_ents_list": [
